'''HMS ''Lion''''' (or ''Lyon'') was a stores [[Hoy (boat)|hoy]] launched in 1709. She was wrecked at [[Port Isaac]] on 26 August 1752.<ref name=Winfield>Winfield (2008), pp.367.</ref>
''Lion'' was under the command of Samuel Wakerel, master. All of her crew was saved, as was some of her cargo of lumber.<ref>Hepper (1994), p. 39.</ref>
